Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech at Fisk University in Nashville, Tennessee. She expressed her love for the city and thanked Mayor Cooper for his leadership during the recent tornadoes. Harris praised Fisk University's legacy of producing national and global leaders, mentioning John Lewis and Diane Nash as examples. She highlighted the importance of leadership and the need for voices to be heard in a democracy. Harris recognized three Tennessee lawmakers who showed courage in the face of gun violence and emphasized the need for smart gun safety laws, including background checks and restrictions on assault weapons. She called for leaders with the courage to act and urged young leaders to take up the cause. Harris ended by saying that they will not be defeated and will continue to fight for freedom and justice.